Peste des petits ruminants, China (People's Rep. of)
----------------------------------------------------
Information received on 26 Mar 2014 from Dr Zhang Zhongqui, Director General, China Animal Disease Control Centre, Veterinary Bureau, Ministry of Agriculture, Beijing, China (People's Rep. of)

Summary
Report type: follow-up report no 8
Date of start of the event: 05 Dec 2013
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 05 Dec 2013
Report date: 25 Mar 2014
Date submitted to OIE: 26 Mar 2014
Reason for notification: 1st occurrence of a listed disease
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Peste des petits ruminants virus
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (basic), laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Jinzu village, Dongkou county, Shaoyang city, Hunan
Date of start of the outbreak: 11 Mar 2014
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Sheep & goats / 360 / 360 / 234 / 126 / 0 /
Outbreak statistics [apparent, rates expressed as percentages]
Species / morbidity rate / mortality rate / case fatality rate / proportion susceptible animals lost*
Sheep & goats / 100 / 65 / 65 / 100
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Control measures
Measures applied: stamping out, quarantine, movement control inside the country, screening, zoning, disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s), dipping/spraying, no vaccination, no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: National Research Center for Exotic Animal Diseases (regional reference laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Sheep & goats / enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay (ELISA) / 25 Mar 2014 / Positive
Sheep & goats / reverse transcription-polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR) / 25 Mar 2014 / Positive

